    "content_hash": "2eef007034216b9c",
    "department": "GTM",
    "description": "About the Company\n\nWhy We Built Lyric: Supply chains are more critical and complex than ever. Every day, large enterprises navigate trillions of possible decisions that could impact the bottom line. Powerful algorithms and AI can address these problems, yet most organizations struggle to leverage supply chain AI at scale. The current SCM technologies are either rigid, limited-scope point solutions or custom solutions built in-house, which demand immense expertise and investment.\n\nThat is…until now.\n\nEnter Lyric: Lyric is an enterprise AI platform built specifically for supply chains, offering the best of both worlds:\n\n - Out-of-the-box AI solutions for optimizing networks, allocating inventory, scheduling routes, planning fulfillment capacity, promising orders, propagating demand, building predictions, analyzing scenarios, and more, plus\n\n - A platform-first approach that empowers both business and technical users with end-to-end product composability, leveraging no-code tools, their own code, or even forking our code to build and refine supply chain decision intelligence\n\nWith Lyric, enterprises no longer have to choose between flexibility and speed, they get both.\n\nThe Mission: We’re building a new era in supply chain with the team best equipped to lead it. With over 20 years at the intersection of supply chain and algorithms, we developed a deep conviction that global supply chains needed something like Lyric. Since our inception in December 2021, that conviction has been validated time and time again.\n\nToday, a growing number of Fortune 500 companies, including Smurfit WestRock, Estée Lauder, Coca-Cola, and more, are innovating on their own terms with Lyric. We can’t wait to see what our customers, both current and future, are empowered to build with us next. Come build with us!\n\n\nROLE OVERVIEW\n\nWe are looking for a Senior Visual Designer who can operate at the intersection of brand, storytelling, and business impact.\n\nYou will work directly with US-based marketing leadership and play a critical role in shaping how Lyric presents itself—across presentations, social media, and overall brand expression.\n\nThis is not a production-only role. You will be expected to think, challenge, and elevate—turning complex ideas into clear, compelling visual narratives.\n\n\n\nWHAT YOU WILL DO\n\n\n1. EXECUTIVE \u0026 SALES PRESENTATIONS\n\n - Design high-impact pitch decks, investor decks, and executive presentations\n\n - Translate complex supply chain + AI concepts into clear visual stories\n\n - Partner with leadership to refine structure, flow, and messaging—not just visuals\n\n - Bring a consultative design approach, not just execution\n\n\n2. SOCIAL MEDIA \u0026 MARKETING CREATIVES\n\n - Own visual design for LinkedIn, website assets, campaigns, and product marketing\n\n - Create scroll-stopping, high-signal creatives aligned with a premium B2B brand\n\n - Work closely with content and growth teams to iterate quickly and test what works\n\n\n3. BRAND DIRECTION \u0026 CONSISTENCY\n\n - Help evolve and enforce Lyric’s visual identity and design system\n\n - Ensure consistency across all external touchpoints\n\n - Push the brand toward a clean, modern, global SaaS aesthetic (not cluttered, not generic)\n\n\n4. CROSS-FUNCTIONAL COLLABORATION\n\n - Work with US marketing leadership, founders, product, and sales teams\n\n - Operate in a fast-paced environment with tight feedback loops\n\n - Balance speed + quality + business context\n   \n\n\nWHAT WE’RE LOOKING FOR\n\n\nCORE SKILLS\n\n - 6-10 years of experience in visual design / brand design / marketing design\n\n - Strong portfolio across:\n   \n   - Presentation design (must-have)\n   \n   - Social media creatives\n   \n   - Brand systems / visual identity\n\n - Expert in tools like:\n   \n   - Figma\n   \n   - Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator, After Effects optional)\n   \n   - Presentation tools (PowerPoint, Google Slides—at a high level)\n\n\nDESIGN THINKING\n\n - Ability to simplify complex ideas visually\n\n - Strong sense of:\n   \n   - Layout\n   \n   - Typography\n   \n   - Color systems\n   \n   - Visual hierarchy\n\n - Can move between:\n   \n   - Minimal, clean SaaS design\n   \n   - High-impact storytelling visuals\n\n\nMINDSET\n\n - Not just a “designer”—a visual storyteller\n\n - Comfortable working with senior stakeholders\n\n - High ownership: you don’t wait for pixel-perfect briefs\n\n - Able to handle ambiguity and shape direction\n\n - Strong taste—you know what good looks like\n   \n\n\nWHAT WILL MAKE YOU STAND OUT\n\n - Experience working with global SaaS / B2B brands\n\n - Strong presentation design samples (this will be heavily evaluated)\n\n - Exposure to AI / data / enterprise products\n\n - Ability to bring motion, interaction, or storytelling layers\n\n - Opinionated about design—not afraid to push back\n   \n\n\nWHY THIS ROLE MATTERS\n\nAt Lyric, design directly influences:\n\n - How we win enterprise deals\n\n - How we communicate complex products\n\n - How we position ourselves globally\n\nYou will be shaping the visual language of a fast-scaling AI company.",
